let me know!  Thanks all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://www.planettom.com/eq/elanaloral.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D7CFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uchassaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chassaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(7/20/01 10:37:19 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_blush.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Intelligence vs Charisma</span><hr size=1> Well, from what I can tell from my 59 levels of being an enchanter is that the effects of charisma are very slight.  The general rule of thumb I've found is that if you can keep your CHA above 150~160, you're got plenty.  I think from the studies I've seen Tudamorf and a few others do on the enchanter boards at Castersrealm, there is only about a 5 to 10% reduction in resists on Mesmerization spells from 150cha to 200cha.  <br>
<br>
So, I would put more emphasis on INT and having a bigger mana pool.  Once you've got your INT up to where you want it, I'd start working on HP/AC.  The way I look at it, is when I die, 99.9999999999% of the time it isn't because I ran OOM and got clobbered, it's because I ran out of HP and was still at 50% mana or better.  <br>
<br>
So, I started sacrificing my CHA gear for HP/AC gear.  My INT (buffed with Enlightenment) is still over 200 (I think 209 now) and my CHA (buffed with Overwhelming Splendor) is 178.  In a raid situation where I'm getting buffs from everyone (cleric, shaman, ranger, paladin), I can get over 3k hp and a smidge over 800ac.  I really can't tell any difference in the resists from going from 211cha to 178cha.<br>
<br>
So, get your cha up to 150, and then spend the rest of your efforts working on HP, AC, and INT is what I would suggest.<br>
<br>
-Chassaria<br>
<br>
