The age old enchanter discussion, int vs. charisma.  Well, if you were starting an enchanter, I'd say throw everything into int.  Because its a well-known fact int is much more expensive than charisma.  Well, until you hit plane's gear where charisma seems to be the lacking factor.<br>
<br>
As for the utility of either of the attributes, you may see 20-page essays explaining why high intelligence doesn't mean much.  Those things take every single aspect of the mana pool and disect it into such a science that even I can't understand it.  So, here's a simple explanation that I have used since I was a wee babe of an enchanter.<br>
<br>
Intelligence is your base mana, and once it hits 200 you're only absorbing ~1 mana per int point.  Charisma, however, is a stat which purely effects the randomness of resists and *charm*.  Charm, in my opinion, is the only thing that can take the clockwork out of an enchanter's life.  Using it in exp groups make it a lot more fun, and you're adding that much more to the group.  You get people who say &quot;DON'T USE CHARM&quot;.  Tell them to not use dots, it can mess up mez if they use it wrong.  It's your class, being told how to play is under no one's jurisdiction.  Unless they are your own class and level, then its constructive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   /Tangent OFF.  Get your intelligence to 200 first.  It's the one you're going to see the most use in, and in having your mana so high it will help in those situations when you would otherwise be OOM.  Charisma should be 150+ if you already are lucky enough to have it that high.  Most buffs can bump it to 200+ with little or no problem after Radiant Visage (34).<br>
<br>
As far as the HP/AC thing goes... it's pure bullshit.  Simply put, its like throwing a glass of water at a forest fire.  You're NOT GOING TO DO ANYTHING.  I was lucky enough to hold on to an orb of infinite void, had BoF (57 cleric AC), and those HP/AC rings.  You know what?  When Unslowed_Froglok79, 80, and 92 beat on me, I didn't have any visible spare time to stun/mez the critters.  But, having 255 charisma (with 56 buff) my charms had a much longer duration than without the buff (~195 charisma).<br>
<br>
<br>
If you find yourself at a comfortable place in int and cha, and are 50+ doing big raids... It's all about resist gear.  Trust me, Trakanon will hit you for 650 each time even with your orb, shield, 21 AC Hate robe, fire emerald rings, and blah... But his 1200 DD/DoT poison spell will completely fly over your head with a good 200+ poison save.<br>
<br>
So...<br>
<br>
Int - Priority<br>
Charisma - After 150, novelty (unless your a charm fiend, like me)<br>
HP/AC gear - Crap, useless, waste of money better spent on TWINKING<br>
Resist gear - PRIORITY while raiding 50+<br>
